'''English'''

'''Etymology'''
from Latin cella, chamber, + vision, from Latin visio, vision or seeing, noun of action from perfect passive participle visus, that which is seen, from verb videre, see, + action noun suffix -io.

'''Noun'''
cellevision, sometimes abbreviated CV

1.  An electronic communication medium that allows the transmission of real-time or visual images, and often sound to wireless handheld electronic devices. 

  ''I became bored while waiting in the airport so I watched a little cellevision.
''

2. Collectively, the programs broadcast via cellevision.

    ''... fifty seven channels and nothing on '''[cellevision]'''.''